{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/childwatchsourcenew(pid:)"]}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"text":"Creates a new child watch source.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/childWatchSourceNew(pid:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"childWatchSourceNew","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"pid"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GPid","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GPid","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib9SourceRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"SourceRef"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The source will not initially be associated with any","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true},{"text":"] and must be added to one with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Source.attach"},{"type":"text","text":"] before it will be executed."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that child watch sources can only be used in conjunction with"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_spawn...","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" when the [flags","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.SpawnFlags.DO_NOT_REAP_CHILD"},{"text":"] flag is used.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that on platforms where [type"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Pid"},{"text":"] must be explicitly closed","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(see [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.spawn_close_pid"},{"text":"]) ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pid"},{"text":" must not be closed while the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"source is still active. Typically, you will want to call","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.spawn_close_pid"},{"type":"text","text":"] in the callback function for the source."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On POSIX platforms, the following restrictions apply to this API","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"due to limitations in POSIX process interfaces:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"pid","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" must be a child of this process."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pid"},{"type":"text","text":" must be positive."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The application must not call "},{"identifier":"man:waitpid(1)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" with a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"non-positive first argument, for instance in another thread.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The application must not wait for ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pid"},{"type":"text","text":" to exit by any other"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"mechanism, including "},{"code":"waitpid(pid, ...)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or a second child-watch","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"source for the same ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pid"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The application must not ignore "},{"code":"SIGCHLD","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before 2.78, the application could not send a signal ("},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"man:kill(2)"},{"text":") to the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"watched ","type":"text"},{"code":"pid","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in a race free manner. Since 2.78, you can do that while the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"associated [struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] is acquired."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before 2.78, even after destroying the [struct"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":"], you could not","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"be sure that ","type":"text"},{"code":"pid","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" wasn’t already reaped. Hence, it was also not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"safe to ","type":"text"},{"code":"kill()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"waitpid()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" on the process ID after the child watch"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"source was gone. Destroying the source before it fired made it"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"impossible to reliably reap the process.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If any of those conditions are not met, this and related APIs will","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not work correctly. This can often be diagnosed via a GLib warning"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"stating that "},{"code":"ECHILD","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" was received by ","type":"text"},{"code":"waitpid()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Calling ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"man:waitpid(2)","type":"reference"},{"text":" for specific processes other than ","type":"text"},{"code":"pid","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"remains a valid thing to do."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"childWatchSourceNew","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"pid","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GPid","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GPid"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SourceRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib9SourceRefV"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"symbolKind":"func","roleHeading":"Function","externalID":"s:4GLib19childWatchSourceNew3pidAA0D3RefVSgs5Int32V_tF","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"childWatchSourceNew(pid:)"},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Source":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Source","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/source","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Source","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GSource","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data type","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"representing an event source."}],"title":"Source","type":"topic"},"man:kill(2)":{"title":"kill()","identifier":"man:kill(2)","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"kill()"}],"url":"man:kill(2)"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":